# Development Done Log

Whenever you finish a task, feature, sprint, or **plan.md phase**, update 
`docs/development-done.md` **before ending the turn**.

Do this for partial completions too (e.g. Phase 4 hero done, carousel still pending) — note what remains.

## When to update

- A phase from `plan.md` is completed or partially completed
- Meaningful files were added, removed, or changed
- Functionality was implemented, fixed, or verified
- Do **not** skip this update after coding work

## Entry format

Append a new section at the **end** of the log (oldest first, newest last), using:

```markdown
## [YYYY-MM-DD] Phase X — Short title

### Functionality covered
- Bullet list of what now works

### Quick summary
1–3 sentences: what was done and why it matters.

### Files added / changed
- `path/to/file` — brief note (added | modified | deleted)

### Status
Completed | Partial — what is left next

### Testing done (if any)
- Checks performed
```

## Rules

- Be accurate — only list work actually completed in this session/step
- Use real file paths relative to the project root
- Keep summaries concise; prefer bullets over paragraphs
- If `docs/development-done.md` is empty, add a short `# Cleanvo — Development Done` heading first, then the entry
- Do not remove or reorder older entries; always append new entries at the **end**
